1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,500
I've heard stories, but I never imagined it would be like this.

2
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:05,320
This place holds secrets.

3
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:07,800
I know it.

4
00:00:08,260 --> 00:00:09,560
She only needed one interview.

5
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:13,280
Jago  Quint  was  the  billionaire  no  one  could  reach,  and  that

6
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:14,640
story  could  save  her  career.

7
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:18,360
So  she  accepted  the  most  dangerous  deal  of  her  life,  pretending

8
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:19,840
to  be  his  girlfriend  for  one

9
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:20,220
night.

10
00:00:20,640 --> 00:00:21,920
It was supposed to be simple.

11
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:25,520
Walk  into  the  ball  convinces  family  and  walk  out  with  the  answers  she

12
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:26,640
needed,  but  when

13
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:29,960
Jago's  mother  demanded  proof  of  love  in  front  of  everyone,  she

14
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:30,880
did  exactly  what  she

15
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:31,700
shouldn't have.

16
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:32,800
She kissed Jago.

17
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:36,080
And  that  kiss,  which  was  only  supposed  to  be  a  lie,

18
00:00:36,620 --> 00:00:38,300
started  to  feel  far  too  real.

19
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:40,500
Hi, I'm Rowan.

20
00:00:40,860 --> 00:00:43,880
A  special  shout  out  to  those  of  you  watching  Book  One  for  free  here  on  the

21
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:44,840
My  Stories  platform,

22
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:47,420
completely ad-free and uninterrupted.

23
00:00:49,730 --> 00:00:52,090
Chapter One, The Impossible Interview.

24
00:00:53,110 --> 00:00:56,270
His  room  smelled  of  reheated  coffee  and  old  paper,

25
00:00:56,750 --> 00:00:58,390
and  Rowina  Pike  had  already  drunk

26
00:00:58,390 --> 00:01:00,370
three cups before nine in the morning.

27
00:01:00,830 --> 00:01:05,590
The gray light coming through the window gave every face their the same shade of exhaustion.

28
00:01:06,190 --> 00:01:10,910
The kind of fatigue that doesn't come from one bad night's sleep, but from months, piled

29
00:01:10,910 --> 00:01:12,230
one on top of another.

30
00:01:12,610 --> 00:01:14,590
She knew, hers was no different.

31
00:01:14,990 --> 00:01:19,610
She held her folder against her chest, and crossed the narrow aisle between the desks,

32
00:01:19,610 --> 00:01:22,250
greeting with a Kurt Nord anyone who looked up.

33
00:01:22,670 --> 00:01:26,750
Wallace Vaughn was waiting for her with his elbows planted on the desk, glasses pushed

34
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:27,870
to the tip of his nose.

35
00:01:28,410 --> 00:01:32,550
The editor had a peculiar way of looking at people, as if he were checking whether they

36
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:33,850
were worth their own salary.

37
00:01:34,430 --> 00:01:38,970
Rowina shut the door behind her, ignored the chair he didn't offer, and sat down without

38
00:01:38,970 --> 00:01:39,990
waiting for an invitation.

39
00:01:40,470 --> 00:01:41,870
I need the interview Pike.

40
00:01:42,410 --> 00:01:46,550
Wallace didn't waste time on introductions, and I need something else too.

41
00:01:46,550 --> 00:01:50,430
If you're about to tell me you need a photo of Quint without his jacket, I'm walking

42
00:01:50,430 --> 00:01:51,810
out of this room right now.

43
00:01:52,130 --> 00:01:52,990
I need a file.

44
00:01:53,510 --> 00:01:57,630
The sentence landed in the middle of the desk, like something too heavy for the furniture.

45
00:01:58,210 --> 00:02:03,150
Rowina raised an eyebrow, waiting for him to refraise to apologise to turn it into a joke.

46
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:04,910
Wallace did none of that.

47
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:09,850
He simply laced his fingers, and kept looking at her, as if he were collecting on an old

48
00:02:09,850 --> 00:02:10,170
debt.

49
00:02:10,690 --> 00:02:11,790
Proof, he added.

50
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:14,810
That that empire is hiding something it shouldn't be hiding.

51
00:02:14,810 --> 00:02:16,790
Everyone hides something Pike.

52
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:18,590
You just need to find out what.

53
00:02:19,070 --> 00:02:22,970
You want me to get inside the home of the most closed off family in the south.

54
00:02:23,330 --> 00:02:27,810
Land the interview no one's managed to land in 10 years, and still walk out of there with

55
00:02:27,810 --> 00:02:28,830
compromising material.

56
00:02:29,370 --> 00:02:31,910
I'm telling you that your job here depends on it.

57
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:33,450
She didn't answer right away.

58
00:02:33,670 --> 00:02:36,210
She sat staring at the coffee stain on the rim of his mug.

59
00:02:36,730 --> 00:02:41,570
Calculating how much of next month's salary was already committed to rent, how much was still

60
00:02:41,570 --> 00:02:42,770
owed on her mother's bill.

61
00:02:42,770 --> 00:02:46,210
The window behind Hollis let in the muffled noise of the street.

62
00:02:46,770 --> 00:02:48,010
A horn, a quick step.

63
00:02:48,490 --> 00:02:52,530
The city running nonstop while she sat there deciding how far she was willing to go.

64
00:02:52,850 --> 00:02:57,230
Then she nodded once, short, like someone signing a contract they haven't yet read.

65
00:02:57,810 --> 00:03:02,230
Marlow Trent intercepted her in the hallway with two fresh coffees, and a smile that was

66
00:03:02,230 --> 00:03:03,070
already a question.

67
00:03:03,610 --> 00:03:08,570
Marlow was a copy editor, a colleague of three years, and the only person in the newsroom

68
00:03:08,570 --> 00:03:12,190
who understood when Rowine needed silence and when she needed noise.

69
00:03:12,770 --> 00:03:14,890
You look like someone who just sold her soul.

70
00:03:15,190 --> 00:03:17,330
Marlow remarked, handing over the hot-a-cup.

71
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:18,470
Was it for much?

72
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:20,410
It was for next month's rent.

73
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:26,270
Marlow laughed, a short laugh, cut off halfway by the awareness that the joke was worth

74
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:28,130
more to herself than to Rowine.

75
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:32,970
She leaned her shoulder against Rowine as they walked down the hallway, and for a moment,

76
00:03:33,570 --> 00:03:35,890
Rowine felt like dropping everything right there.

77
00:03:35,890 --> 00:03:38,810
Walking out the front door, and never coming back.

78
00:03:39,110 --> 00:03:39,790
She didn't.

79
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:42,250
She drank the coffee until it burned her tongue.

80
00:03:42,810 --> 00:03:46,350
After noon came quickly, and with it a note left at the front desk.

81
00:03:46,770 --> 00:03:51,750
No sender, just her name on the front of the envelope, written in black pen and handwriting

82
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:57,370
that wasn't a friend, slanted controlled letters, each one in its exact place.

83
00:03:57,870 --> 00:04:02,550
Rowine had turned the envelope over twice before opening it, inside just an address and

84
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:03,090
a time.

85
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:04,130
Nothing more.

86
00:04:04,130 --> 00:04:09,190
The office it pointed to was three blocks away, in a discreet building she had never noticed,

87
00:04:09,670 --> 00:04:11,950
despite having walked past it hundreds of times.

88
00:04:12,550 --> 00:04:16,950
The sign at the entrance simply read Ashford and Associates, in letters too small to draw

89
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:17,390
attention.

90
00:04:18,030 --> 00:04:22,050
Rowine had climbed the steps with her folder still pressed against her chest, and greeted

91
00:04:22,050 --> 00:04:24,190
the receptionist with the name that was on the note.

92
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:26,970
The man who received her was younger than she expected.

93
00:04:27,530 --> 00:04:32,030
Tall, navy, suit, no tie, with that kind of discretion only old money teachers.

94
00:04:32,030 --> 00:04:37,130
The extended his hand and introduced himself as Silas Ashford, the Quint family's lawyer,

95
00:04:37,490 --> 00:04:39,850
a friend of Jago's since their boarding school days.

96
00:04:40,310 --> 00:04:44,490
The information came without fanfare, the way someone hands over a business card.

97
00:04:44,950 --> 00:04:45,930
Have a seat, Miss Pike.

98
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:49,010
His voice had the same tone as the handwriting on the envelope.

99
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:51,510
I'll be brief because the proposal is brief.

100
00:04:51,970 --> 00:04:52,590
I'm curious.

101
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:58,210
Mr. Quint agrees to grant a two-hour interview to your publication, no restrictions

102
00:04:58,210 --> 00:05:00,630
on subject matter, except one.

103
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:02,610
Silas made a minimal pause.

104
00:05:03,070 --> 00:05:07,050
The kind of pause lawyers used to let the client swallow the next piece of information.

105
00:05:07,670 --> 00:05:12,690
In return, you would attend the family's Gallaboll in Savannah as his companion on Friday.

106
00:05:13,290 --> 00:05:15,090
One night, just one.

107
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:18,290
Rowine elapsed before her brain authorized her mouth.

108
00:05:19,030 --> 00:05:19,590
Companion.

109
00:05:20,150 --> 00:05:21,410
That's the word he preferred.

110
00:05:21,990 --> 00:05:23,570
And what word didn't he prefer?

111
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:28,490
The corner of Silas's mouth moved half a millimeter, almost the beginning of a smile

112
00:05:28,490 --> 00:05:29,850
but nothing followed through.

113
00:05:29,850 --> 00:05:34,610
He slid a black envelope across the desk, sealed, with her name written on the front

114
00:05:34,610 --> 00:05:38,330
in the same slanted, controlled handwriting as the first note.

115
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:43,610
Letters she now recognized without effort and which definitely did not belong to Silas.

116
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:45,250
The rules are in there.

117
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,430
One read is enough.

118
00:05:46,810 --> 00:05:48,210
He expects an answer today.

119
00:05:48,730 --> 00:05:50,910
Rowine looked at the black envelope for too long.

120
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:52,450
She thought about the rent.

121
00:05:52,870 --> 00:05:55,090
She thought about the look on Holis's face.

122
00:05:55,290 --> 00:05:58,130
She thought about the old photograph of the reclusive billionaire

123
00:05:58,130 --> 00:06:00,990
that had circulated through the papers forever.

124
00:06:01,610 --> 00:06:03,790
Always the same profile of a clenched jaw.

125
00:06:04,210 --> 00:06:07,270
Always the same gaze that didn't invite anyone to stay.

126
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:10,690
She tucked the envelope into her folder without opening it.

127
00:06:10,930 --> 00:06:12,610
Tell him I'll be in Savannah on Friday.

128
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:16,390
Silas nodded like someone who already knew the answer before the question.

129
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:21,730
He rose, shook her hand again and walked her to the door with practice courtesy.

130
00:06:22,310 --> 00:06:24,930
Before closing the handle, he said almost without voice.

131
00:06:25,350 --> 00:06:27,150
He's not what the press writes, that's all.

132
00:06:27,150 --> 00:06:29,010
Rowine didn't ask what he meant.

133
00:06:29,310 --> 00:06:30,850
She preferred not to know yet.

134
00:06:31,270 --> 00:06:34,610
Marlo was waiting for her on the street with a cigarette that pretended to be lit.

135
00:06:35,090 --> 00:06:38,190
The kind of theatre she used as an excuse to loiter on corners.

136
00:06:38,770 --> 00:06:41,130
Rowine handed over the black envelope without ceremony.

137
00:06:41,690 --> 00:06:43,850
A friend turned the object over in her hand,

138
00:06:44,330 --> 00:06:47,730
studied the seal with more attention than necessary, and gave it back.

139
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:51,050
Don't open it now, Marlo said, open it on the train.

140
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:52,090
It's prettier that way.

141
00:06:52,490 --> 00:06:52,950
Pretty ya.

142
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:55,750
Do you want to be someone else's story or make history?

143
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:59,090
If it's the second, you open it on the train alone,

144
00:06:59,390 --> 00:07:01,990
and you cry if you need to cry without anyone seeing.

145
00:07:02,450 --> 00:07:03,630
It's the least you deserve.

146
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:06,870
Rowine laughed and the laugh pulled some of the weight off her back.

147
00:07:07,170 --> 00:07:10,050
She rested her forehead on Marlo's shoulder for a short second.

148
00:07:10,550 --> 00:07:13,610
Just enough to remember she still had a friend in that grey city,

149
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:15,370
and then she went home to pack.

150
00:07:15,850 --> 00:07:17,950
The station was too crowded for her taste.

151
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:20,770
Rowine had dragged her luggage between hurried bodies,

152
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:23,130
bought a sandwich she wasn't going to eat,

153
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:25,130
and settled by the window of the car.

154
00:07:25,130 --> 00:07:28,490
The seats smelled of dust and warm synthetic leather.

155
00:07:28,890 --> 00:07:32,330
That smell of a place where many people have passed without leaving a trace.

156
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:34,870
She sat staring at the tracks for a while,

157
00:07:35,170 --> 00:07:38,150
before taking the black envelope out of the inner pocket of her bag.

158
00:07:38,530 --> 00:07:40,590
The seal gave way with a dry sound.

159
00:07:41,130 --> 00:07:43,230
Inside, three folded sheets.

160
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:47,230
The first two carried instructions written with almost legal precision.

161
00:07:47,850 --> 00:07:49,770
Times, names she should memorize,

162
00:07:50,450 --> 00:07:52,230
clothes that would be delivered to the hotel.

163
00:07:52,230 --> 00:07:55,610
What to say if anyone asked how long they had known each other,

164
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:59,110
Rowine erred them with the same attention she gave to story contracts,

165
00:07:59,810 --> 00:08:01,130
mentally noting every detail,

166
00:08:01,590 --> 00:08:02,990
every gap between the lines.

167
00:08:03,590 --> 00:08:08,430
The third sheet was smaller, a single line written by hand, unsigned.

168
00:08:08,990 --> 00:08:11,150
Don't smile at anyone like you believe it.

169
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:12,610
Only smile when I'm looking.

170
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:14,190
She read it three times.

171
00:08:14,590 --> 00:08:15,590
She put it away again.

172
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:20,050
She looked out the window as the train picked up speed and the city opened into suburb,

173
00:08:20,050 --> 00:08:21,090
then countryside,

174
00:08:21,790 --> 00:08:22,310
then nothing.

175
00:08:22,890 --> 00:08:26,970
And she couldn't decide whether that was an order, a warning, or a request.

176
00:08:27,570 --> 00:08:29,710
The train arrived in Savannah in the late afternoon.

177
00:08:30,290 --> 00:08:32,970
The air changed before she even stepped onto the platform.

178
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:35,070
Warmer, denser,

179
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:37,930
laid in with a sweet perfume she couldn't yet name.

180
00:08:38,470 --> 00:08:41,550
Magnolia maybe, or something that grew near water.

181
00:08:41,950 --> 00:08:44,650
Rowine across the station with her folder under her arm,

182
00:08:45,090 --> 00:08:47,990
looking for the driver who would be waiting with her name on a sign.

183
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:53,290
She found the dark car outside, a man in a suit opening the back door without ceremony.

184
00:08:53,890 --> 00:08:58,610
Before getting in, she looked one last time at the city's skyline and saw in the distance,

185
00:08:59,210 --> 00:09:03,590
the high roof of the quint mansion cut against the sky that was beginning to turn orange.

186
00:09:04,070 --> 00:09:08,230
Too big, too old, the kind of house that doesn't invite you in.

187
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:09,530
It absorbs you.

188
00:09:09,970 --> 00:09:11,350
Rowine sat on the leather seat,

189
00:09:11,810 --> 00:09:13,710
rested her head against the cold glass,

190
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:16,330
and pressed the black envelope against her lap,

191
00:09:16,330 --> 00:09:19,410
like someone clutching a boarding pass to another country.

192
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:21,810
She took the sheet out one more time.

193
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:23,810
Only smile when I'm looking.

194
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:26,810
She re-read it, folded it, put it away.

195
00:09:27,350 --> 00:09:32,590
The car started up, and the streets of Savannah began to pass by outside like a borrowed set,

196
00:09:32,890 --> 00:09:37,410
with the moss heavy trees and the old houses that each guarded their own version of a secret.

197
00:09:37,830 --> 00:09:40,550
And for the first time since Holly's Vaughn had uttered the word,

198
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:42,590
file, Rowine a pike wondered,

199
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:46,370
whether she could go home as the same person who had boarded the train.

200
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:49,690
The chapter 2, a three second kiss.

201
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:53,750
Hotel suite was bigger than her entire apartment,

202
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:57,370
with a soft smell of jasmine that seemed built into the walls.

203
00:09:57,930 --> 00:10:00,810
Rowine looked at herself in the oval mirror for a long time,

204
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:04,730
adjusting the wine-colored silk dress they had left hanging behind the door.

205
00:10:05,130 --> 00:10:06,650
The fabric fell effortlessly.

206
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:11,010
The kind of piece that only existed when someone paid for it without thinking twice.

207
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:14,750
The driver knocked at the door at the exact time indicated in the envelope.

208
00:10:15,350 --> 00:10:19,210
Rowine went down, crossed the lobby under stairs she pretended not to notice,

209
00:10:19,590 --> 00:10:21,350
and found the car waiting at the curb.

210
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:24,070
The back door opened before she touched the handle,

211
00:10:24,470 --> 00:10:28,090
and the first thing she saw inside was the impeccable crease of dark trousers,

212
00:10:28,730 --> 00:10:30,970
running down to a pair of polished black shoes.

213
00:10:31,490 --> 00:10:33,770
Jago Quint was seated on the other side of the seat,

214
00:10:34,210 --> 00:10:38,270
with one knee slightly apart from the other, hands resting on his own thighs.

215
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:41,190
He didn't stand, didn't extend his hand.

216
00:10:41,610 --> 00:10:45,050
He merely tilted his chin and inch toward the empty spot beside him,

217
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:45,770
and waited.

218
00:10:46,490 --> 00:10:49,410
Rowine got in, adjusted her skirt with a quick gesture,

219
00:10:50,010 --> 00:10:52,190
and shut the door with more force than necessary.

220
00:10:52,770 --> 00:10:53,230
He noticed.

221
00:10:53,770 --> 00:10:54,890
She saw that he noticed.

222
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:56,530
Neither of them commented.

223
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:58,150
Good evening Miss Pike.

224
00:10:58,570 --> 00:11:01,970
His voice was lower than she had imagined from any interview she'd ever read.

225
00:11:02,470 --> 00:11:05,050
A voice that didn't rise because it didn't need to.

226
00:11:05,050 --> 00:11:08,490
Rowine returned her face and looked at him full on for the first time,

227
00:11:08,890 --> 00:11:12,670
and had the displeasure of confirming that the portraits published over the years did

228
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:13,470
him no justice.

229
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:16,910
In person, he was a sculpture of a straight jaw,

230
00:11:17,310 --> 00:11:19,850
dark hair combed back with calculated carelessness,

231
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:24,570
and eyes that decided the temperature of the room before saying anything at all.

232
00:11:24,910 --> 00:11:26,050
Good evening Mr. Quint.

233
00:11:26,550 --> 00:11:27,510
Jago will do.

234
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:28,990
Then Rowine will do.

235
00:11:29,310 --> 00:11:32,550
He nodded almost imperceptibly, the car started up,

236
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:35,150
and for a while the two of them sat in silence.

237
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:37,850
Rowine noticed his hands resting on his knees,

238
00:11:38,370 --> 00:11:41,390
long fingers, a silver watch with no visible brand.

239
00:11:41,870 --> 00:11:45,130
She also noticed that the seat between them held a thin leather folder,

240
00:11:45,430 --> 00:11:48,150
closed, with one corner leaning against the glass.

241
00:11:48,690 --> 00:11:49,170
Details.

242
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:50,870
She collected details.

243
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:52,470
Are the rules clear?

244
00:11:52,690 --> 00:11:54,250
He asked without turning his face.

245
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:55,010
Crystal.

246
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:56,030
Any questions?

247
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:57,030
One.

248
00:11:57,690 --> 00:12:00,190
Rowine awaited until he finally turned his gaze to her.

249
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:02,630
How long do you intend for this night to last?

250
00:12:03,110 --> 00:12:05,470
As long as necessary, that's not an answer.

251
00:12:05,930 --> 00:12:07,050
It's the only one I have.

252
00:12:07,370 --> 00:12:11,190
He looked forward again and Rowine accepted defeat in that round without arguing.

253
00:12:11,690 --> 00:12:14,390
She kept watching his profile against the dark window.

254
00:12:14,810 --> 00:12:19,610
The hard line of his jaw, the way his thumb pressed against his own knee in a steady rhythm,

255
00:12:19,990 --> 00:12:22,250
like someone counting something inside himself.

256
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:25,450
She stored the gesture in her memory, and said nothing.

257
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:29,090
The Quint mentioned appeared at the end of the avenue of tall trees,

258
00:12:29,090 --> 00:12:31,430
lit from outside like a theatre set.

259
00:12:31,890 --> 00:12:34,110
Rowine drew a deep breath before the car stopped.

260
00:12:34,710 --> 00:12:35,810
Jago got out first.

261
00:12:36,210 --> 00:12:40,270
Went around the vehicle and opened her door with a courtesy that sounded more rehearsed

262
00:12:40,270 --> 00:12:40,950
than sincere.

263
00:12:41,450 --> 00:12:42,510
He offered his arm.

264
00:12:42,890 --> 00:12:43,490
She accepted.

265
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:47,810
His palm brushed briefly against her hand as he helped her position herself,

266
00:12:48,230 --> 00:12:49,510
and the temperature changed.

267
00:12:50,010 --> 00:12:52,170
Don't smile at anyone like you believe it.

268
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:53,030
He murmured.

269
00:12:53,290 --> 00:12:55,890
Barely moving his lips as they climb the steps.

270
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:57,850
You already warned me in writing.

271
00:12:57,850 --> 00:12:59,610
I'm reinforcing it.

272
00:12:59,890 --> 00:13:02,190
The main hall swallowed them the moment the door opened.

273
00:13:02,810 --> 00:13:04,670
Rowine smelled it before she saw anything.

274
00:13:05,230 --> 00:13:06,730
Magnolia and old money.

275
00:13:07,310 --> 00:13:10,030
Exactly as Silas had said in the instruction note.

276
00:13:10,450 --> 00:13:13,450
The white walls rose high to a ceiling of worked stucco,

277
00:13:13,970 --> 00:13:17,910
and everywhere there were antique chandeliers spreading a honey-colored light over the guests.

278
00:13:18,530 --> 00:13:22,650
Long dresses, emerald chocas, men in black tuxedoes,

279
00:13:22,810 --> 00:13:24,330
greeting each other without enthusiasm.

280
00:13:24,890 --> 00:13:27,650
Jago introduced her to three couples in a row,

281
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:29,710
always with the same assembled sentence.

282
00:13:30,290 --> 00:13:31,690
My companion for the evening.

283
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:32,930
Rowine a pike.

284
00:13:33,450 --> 00:13:34,910
No complicated surnames.

285
00:13:35,430 --> 00:13:36,030
No deer.

286
00:13:36,590 --> 00:13:37,150
No love.

287
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:39,550
Rowine a smile in just the right measure.

288
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:42,150
Answered questions in just the right measure.

289
00:13:42,670 --> 00:13:43,570
And noticed everything.

290
00:13:44,090 --> 00:13:46,090
She noticed that he avoided the terrace.

291
00:13:46,550 --> 00:13:49,890
Twice a waiter passed offering to take guests out to the outdoor area.

292
00:13:50,310 --> 00:13:51,770
And both times Jago declined,

293
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:54,070
with a minimal gesture of his chin,

294
00:13:54,490 --> 00:13:56,110
without even looking at the glass door.

295
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:59,470
She also noticed that his gaze had one point,

296
00:13:59,850 --> 00:14:01,670
tripped over an empty chair near the window.

297
00:14:02,210 --> 00:14:04,110
A chair upholstered in dark green velvet,

298
00:14:04,630 --> 00:14:06,510
slightly set apart from the rest of the arrangement,

299
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:10,430
as if it belonged to someone who used to sit there and hadn't arrived yet.

300
00:14:10,610 --> 00:14:11,550
He looked away quickly.

301
00:14:12,170 --> 00:14:13,170
Rowine a stored it.

302
00:14:13,450 --> 00:14:14,610
What an unlikely evening.

303
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:18,290
The voice came from behind her sweetest syrup heated too much.

304
00:14:18,650 --> 00:14:21,590
Rowine a turned and found a woman with red hair pinned in a low

305
00:14:21,590 --> 00:14:25,890
one, an emerald green dress, a smile that didn't reach her eyes.

306
00:14:26,450 --> 00:14:28,150
Jago stiffened beside her.

307
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:30,450
Odeit, he greeted her without warmth.

308
00:14:30,930 --> 00:14:31,370
Jago.

309
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:33,950
Odeit Mashaan extended her hand to Rowine,

310
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:37,650
palm down the gesture of someone expecting reverence,

311
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:38,950
and the companion.

312
00:14:39,570 --> 00:14:40,110
How interesting.

313
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:41,610
What do you do dear?

314
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:42,670
I write.

315
00:14:43,310 --> 00:14:46,150
A. Odeit seemed to decide something in silence.

316
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:48,570
How brave of him to bring you here.

317
00:14:48,570 --> 00:14:50,690
Brave of me to agree to come.

318
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:51,690
Odeit laughed.

319
00:14:52,290 --> 00:14:54,290
A short note that contained nothing of laughter.

320
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:56,710
Then she moved off with a wave of her fingers,

321
00:14:57,330 --> 00:14:59,570
leaving behind a trail of expensive perfume.

322
00:15:00,110 --> 00:15:03,170
Jago rested his hand at the small of Rowine's back

323
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:06,890
for just a second, a gesture of ownership that wasn't a

324
00:15:06,890 --> 00:15:07,210
affection.

325
00:15:07,730 --> 00:15:08,770
Then he withdrew it.

326
00:15:08,970 --> 00:15:10,510
You didn't need to provoke her.

327
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:11,550
He remarked.

328
00:15:11,650 --> 00:15:11,890
Low.

329
00:15:12,470 --> 00:15:13,470
I did, actually.

330
00:15:14,090 --> 00:15:14,750
He didn't answer.

331
00:15:15,110 --> 00:15:16,950
But the corner of his mouth moved a millimeter,

332
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:20,430
and Rowine arrested it as if it were the headline of the month.

333
00:15:20,710 --> 00:15:22,090
It wasn't a smile yet.

334
00:15:22,510 --> 00:15:23,350
It was close.

335
00:15:23,950 --> 00:15:26,270
The silence in the hall changed texture.

336
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:28,150
Before she understood why.

337
00:15:28,570 --> 00:15:31,030
It was as if the air had drawn back a few inches,

338
00:15:31,530 --> 00:15:35,350
and everybody there in unison had turned their heads in the same direction.

339
00:15:36,090 --> 00:15:37,710
Rowine followed the others gaze,

340
00:15:38,110 --> 00:15:40,890
and saw Udora quint entering through the main door.

341
00:15:41,270 --> 00:15:43,410
The matriarch didn't need to announce herself.

342
00:15:43,410 --> 00:15:47,810
The long black dress, a pearl necklace that fell to the middle of her chest,

343
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:51,030
gray hair pinned with a rigidity that allowed no discussion.

344
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:53,370
She crossed the hall without greeting anyone,

345
00:15:53,790 --> 00:15:55,830
and stopped before her son and his companion,

346
00:15:56,270 --> 00:15:58,610
with the expression of someone appraising merchandise.

347
00:15:59,450 --> 00:16:01,150
Good evening, mother, said Jago.

348
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:03,330
Udora didn't answer her son.

349
00:16:03,730 --> 00:16:05,330
She turned her pale eyes to Rowine,

350
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:09,810
and examined her from shoes to hairstyle with a surgical calm.

351
00:16:10,210 --> 00:16:11,910
Then she stepped half a step closer,

352
00:16:11,910 --> 00:16:14,190
and the voice that came out of her was low,

353
00:16:14,330 --> 00:16:16,150
but sharp enough to cut the entire hall.

354
00:16:16,670 --> 00:16:18,410
I don't see love here, my son.

355
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:21,090
The silence closed around the three of them.

356
00:16:21,490 --> 00:16:24,090
Rowine felt Jago's body stiffened beside her.

357
00:16:24,330 --> 00:16:26,010
His shoulders rising half an inch.

358
00:16:26,510 --> 00:16:28,830
Udora stayed put, chin raised waiting.

359
00:16:29,410 --> 00:16:30,830
Proof said the matriarch.

360
00:16:31,330 --> 00:16:32,990
If it's true, prove it.

361
00:16:33,270 --> 00:16:34,530
The entire hall turned.

362
00:16:35,070 --> 00:16:36,770
Heads lifted from champagne glasses,

363
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:38,190
conversation ceased.

364
00:16:38,790 --> 00:16:40,190
Waiters stopped where they stood.

365
00:16:40,190 --> 00:16:43,010
Rowine felt the weight of the whole hall falling on her

366
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:44,530
and Jago at the same time.

367
00:16:44,890 --> 00:16:45,670
He locked up.

368
00:16:45,870 --> 00:16:47,130
She saw that he locked up.

369
00:16:47,410 --> 00:16:49,410
His thumb stopped counting on his own hip,

370
00:16:49,690 --> 00:16:50,710
his jaw hardened,

371
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:54,170
and for a whole second, no decision came out of his body.

372
00:16:54,810 --> 00:16:56,030
Rowine had decided for him.

373
00:16:56,150 --> 00:16:58,950
She raised her hand took his face by the side and pulled.

374
00:16:59,370 --> 00:17:03,170
His mouth met hers with a hesitation of someone who hadn't rehearsed this scene,

375
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:06,210
and for an instant, Rowine thought he wouldn't respond.

376
00:17:06,850 --> 00:17:08,210
Then his breath faltered.

377
00:17:08,210 --> 00:17:09,610
She felt the falter.

378
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:12,030
felt the air caught halfway up his chest.

379
00:17:12,430 --> 00:17:16,350
felt his hand rise by reflex to her back and settle between her shoulder blades,

380
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:19,070
with a pressure that didn't belong to the charade.

381
00:17:19,570 --> 00:17:21,570
The kiss was supposed to last a second.

382
00:17:22,030 --> 00:17:23,250
It lasted three.

383
00:17:23,530 --> 00:17:24,350
Maybe more.

384
00:17:24,850 --> 00:17:28,690
Rowine lost count somewhere between the moment he tilted his head a little to the side,

385
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:32,410
and the moment she herself forgot there was a hall around them.

386
00:17:32,610 --> 00:17:35,450
When they pulled apart, she opened her eyes first.

387
00:17:35,850 --> 00:17:37,230
He took half a second longer.

388
00:17:37,230 --> 00:17:40,430
And what Rowine saw on his face when he finally looked back,

389
00:17:40,770 --> 00:17:42,530
was the same thing she felt inside,

390
00:17:43,050 --> 00:17:44,930
and which she wasn't prepared to name yet.

391
00:17:45,390 --> 00:17:47,210
You'daw a stepped back half a step.

392
00:17:47,570 --> 00:17:50,590
She adjusted her pearl necklace with a calculated carelessness,

393
00:17:51,130 --> 00:17:55,070
and the corner of her mouth drew a line that wasn't a smile but pretended to be.

394
00:17:55,210 --> 00:17:55,470
Good.

395
00:17:56,030 --> 00:17:56,970
Mermaid the matriarch.

396
00:17:57,430 --> 00:17:59,050
I hope to see you again many times.

397
00:17:59,650 --> 00:17:59,870
Many.

398
00:18:00,450 --> 00:18:02,230
She turned on her heels and moved off.

399
00:18:02,570 --> 00:18:04,950
The hall little by little began to breathe again.

400
00:18:05,630 --> 00:18:08,050
Conversations returned like a discrete murmur.

401
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:09,030
Waiters moved.

402
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:12,210
Someone laughed in the distance at something that wasn't funny.

403
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,270
Rowine kept looking at Jago.

404
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:17,110
His hand was still on her back forgotten there.

405
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:20,530
In no hurry to leave, he took his time pulling it back.

406
00:18:20,830 --> 00:18:24,230
When he did, his fingers pass slowly over the silk of the dress,

407
00:18:24,350 --> 00:18:27,570
like someone memorizing a path they might need to retrace later.

408
00:18:27,870 --> 00:18:30,930
Across the hall, Odec Marchong watched them with a glass in her hand,

409
00:18:31,270 --> 00:18:33,110
and her smile was now a different one.

410
00:18:33,110 --> 00:18:35,850
Rowine arrested it, stored it.

411
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:38,190
She already knew, without needing a warning,

412
00:18:38,710 --> 00:18:40,330
that that woman would want payback.

413
00:18:40,730 --> 00:18:44,630
Jago leaned in very slightly, and spoke close to her ear so low that

414
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:45,530
only she could hear.

415
00:18:45,890 --> 00:18:47,070
You owe me an explanation.

416
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:48,530
For the kiss?

417
00:18:48,950 --> 00:18:50,050
For the length of the kiss.

418
00:18:50,670 --> 00:18:51,630
Rowine didn't answer.

419
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:53,410
She didn't know the answer yet.

420
00:18:53,650 --> 00:18:54,950
She took the glass away to her,

421
00:18:55,150 --> 00:18:57,710
drank a sip she didn't even feel go down,

422
00:18:58,110 --> 00:19:00,410
and looked again at the empty chair near the window.

423
00:19:00,410 --> 00:19:03,890
Someone, at some point, had sat in it.

424
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:05,930
Someone who now was no longer there,

425
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:09,870
and Rowine a pike, who had collected details since childhood,

426
00:19:10,470 --> 00:19:12,930
understood that the most important story of that night,

427
00:19:13,290 --> 00:19:16,550
had nothing to do with the reason Hollis Vaughan had sent her there.

428
00:19:18,410 --> 00:19:20,850
Chapter 3, Coffee with No Recorder.

429
00:19:22,170 --> 00:19:24,330
The morning after the ball arrived without ceremony,

430
00:19:24,930 --> 00:19:27,950
the Savannah Sun came through the gaps in the curtain of the guest room

431
00:19:27,950 --> 00:19:31,370
at the quint mansion with an almost impolite insistence,

432
00:19:31,770 --> 00:19:36,130
and Rowine applied open her eyes before she remembered exactly where she was.

433
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:39,810
It took a whole instant for the high ceiling, the carved footboard,

434
00:19:40,210 --> 00:19:43,550
and the thick silence of the house to organize themselves in her head.

435
00:19:43,830 --> 00:19:45,610
Only then did the kiss come back.

436
00:19:45,910 --> 00:19:47,750
It came back first through her lip.

437
00:19:48,190 --> 00:19:49,650
Then through the nape of her neck,

438
00:19:50,050 --> 00:19:50,930
then through her stomach.

439
00:19:51,350 --> 00:19:53,870
Three seconds that now carried the weight of biography.

440
00:19:54,470 --> 00:19:56,990
She sat on the edge of the bed and looked at her own hands.

441
00:19:56,990 --> 00:19:58,230
They were cold.

442
00:19:58,770 --> 00:20:01,490
Someone had left a coffee tray on the sideboard beside the door,

443
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:05,190
during the night probably, because the cup was no longer steaming.

444
00:20:05,750 --> 00:20:10,190
Beside it a short note, written by hand in a hand writing she recognized at once,

445
00:20:10,650 --> 00:20:12,070
garden, whenever you can.

446
00:20:12,590 --> 00:20:17,170
Jay Rowine re-read the note twice just to prove to herself that it hadn't unsettled her.

447
00:20:17,370 --> 00:20:18,070
It didn't stick.

448
00:20:18,450 --> 00:20:21,690
The garden was at the back of the house, far from the main hall.

449
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:24,610
She noticed that as a small pay-lide housekeeper,

450
00:20:24,610 --> 00:20:26,630
let her down a corridor of portraits.

451
00:20:27,290 --> 00:20:29,270
The woman introduced herself as Nive,

452
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:33,550
lightly squeezed Rowine's arm and said in an accent from rural Georgia,

453
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:35,730
that Mr. Jago was already waiting.

454
00:20:36,270 --> 00:20:38,390
There was warmth in her voice but also scrutiny.

455
00:20:39,250 --> 00:20:42,030
Rowine smiled with her mouth closed and asked nothing.

456
00:20:42,590 --> 00:20:46,050
Jago Quint was standing near an old rose bush with his back to the house.

457
00:20:46,550 --> 00:20:48,530
White shirt sleeves folded to the elbow,

458
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:50,350
hair still wet from his shower.

459
00:20:50,890 --> 00:20:52,910
He turned when he heard the gravel and for a second,

460
00:20:52,910 --> 00:20:56,350
just one, his eyes met hers unguarded,

461
00:20:56,950 --> 00:20:58,930
without their usual controlled gleam.

462
00:20:59,470 --> 00:21:01,090
Then his jaw firmed up again.

463
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:02,150
Did you sleep?

464
00:21:02,670 --> 00:21:04,310
As much as I could, she answered,

465
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:05,850
the house makes noises.

466
00:21:06,430 --> 00:21:09,750
It does. He pointed with his chin toward a cast iron bench.

467
00:21:10,330 --> 00:21:10,990
Sit with me.

468
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:13,210
We need to work out what comes next.

469
00:21:13,770 --> 00:21:17,530
Rowina obeyed, but chose to sit in profile knees turned outward.

470
00:21:17,970 --> 00:21:19,430
A small defense he noticed.

471
00:21:19,970 --> 00:21:20,730
He said nothing.

472
00:21:20,730 --> 00:21:23,090
You have the interview, Jago began,

473
00:21:23,570 --> 00:21:26,030
his voice low and chosen word by word.

474
00:21:26,530 --> 00:21:27,450
That's still standing,

475
00:21:27,970 --> 00:21:30,190
but last night raised an issue I didn't foresee.

476
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:32,710
My mother didn't believe it until the kiss.

477
00:21:33,170 --> 00:21:34,450
Maybe she believed it afterward.

478
00:21:34,970 --> 00:21:38,030
If you disappear tomorrow, she'll get suspicious again.

479
00:21:38,390 --> 00:21:40,850
And I'll have three candidates on the table by Sunday.

480
00:21:41,250 --> 00:21:42,690
You're asking me for more days.

481
00:21:43,130 --> 00:21:44,250
I'm asking for weeks.

482
00:21:44,850 --> 00:21:48,590
Rowina swallowed the small shock and breathed through her mouth before answering.

483
00:21:48,590 --> 00:21:49,970
Weeks of what?

484
00:21:50,530 --> 00:21:51,030
Appearances.

485
00:21:51,630 --> 00:21:53,070
A dinner here and event there.

486
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:56,890
Enough for Savannah to believe you're the woman who finally got into this house.

487
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:57,670
He paused.

488
00:21:58,250 --> 00:21:59,710
Same payment, same interview.

489
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:01,130
Just a longer timeline.

490
00:22:01,730 --> 00:22:03,030
There was logic in the proposal.

491
00:22:03,550 --> 00:22:04,470
And there was a trap.

492
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:05,610
She knew both.

493
00:22:05,910 --> 00:22:06,730
And if I refuse.

494
00:22:07,410 --> 00:22:10,030
You get the interview anyway, he said without hesitating.

495
00:22:10,610 --> 00:22:13,390
We agreed on something and I don't undo what's agreed.

496
00:22:13,990 --> 00:22:15,590
That was what disarmed her.

497
00:22:15,590 --> 00:22:16,690
Not the proposal.

498
00:22:17,090 --> 00:22:18,650
The resolution of the proposal.

499
00:22:19,270 --> 00:22:20,850
Rowina bit the inside of her cheek.

500
00:22:21,290 --> 00:22:24,030
Looked at the nearest rose, counted to three and said yes.

501
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:25,210
He didn't smile.

502
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:28,670
He just nodded slightly, like someone closing a clause.

503
00:22:29,170 --> 00:22:31,390
But when she stood up to go back into the house,

504
00:22:31,650 --> 00:22:35,950
his hand brushed her back for half a second, had a spot below her shoulder blade.

505
00:22:36,430 --> 00:22:39,190
And lingered an instant longer than any contract required.

506
00:22:39,610 --> 00:22:42,970
She stored the gesture alongside the others she was already collecting.

507
00:22:42,970 --> 00:22:46,710
The following weeks arrived slowly and without a truce.

508
00:22:47,210 --> 00:22:49,470
Rowina began to split herself between the newsroom

509
00:22:49,470 --> 00:22:52,850
where Marlo covered her shifts with increasingly irritated humour

510
00:22:52,850 --> 00:22:57,010
and the streets of Savannah, where she learned there were neighborhoods where the air

511
00:22:57,010 --> 00:23:01,070
smelled of wet jasmine and others where it only smelled of hoarded money.

512
00:23:01,510 --> 00:23:06,070
Jago always sent for her at the station with the same driver and always in the same car.

513
00:23:06,390 --> 00:23:08,870
He waited for her inside in the back seat,

514
00:23:09,250 --> 00:23:11,050
shoulder leaning against the opposite door.

515
00:23:11,050 --> 00:23:15,570
One Tuesday, he took her to an antique's fair under the oaks of the old square.

516
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:18,330
Rowina stopped in front of a tray of loose pendants

517
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:22,310
and picked up one shaped like a crooked owl, half green with age,

518
00:23:22,690 --> 00:23:24,490
set with ridiculous red stones.

519
00:23:25,010 --> 00:23:28,930
It's ugly, she said, smiling at the object as if it were an accomplice.

520
00:23:29,430 --> 00:23:33,030
It is, Jago agreed, she put the pendant back on the tray.

521
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:36,670
She didn't ask for it, didn't haggle, didn't look at it again.

522
00:23:37,210 --> 00:23:39,970
Half an hour later, when they were heading back to the car,

523
00:23:39,970 --> 00:23:43,630
he passed the dark velvet box into her hand without any ceremony

524
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:47,670
and Rowina stood in the middle of the sidewalk, holding the crooked owl

525
00:23:47,670 --> 00:23:49,310
as if it were a live animal.

526
00:23:49,850 --> 00:23:51,730
You didn't haggle, she remarked.

527
00:23:52,010 --> 00:23:54,290
No, he opened the car door for her.

528
00:23:54,470 --> 00:23:55,930
I knew what it was worth to you.

529
00:23:56,170 --> 00:23:59,890
It was that day that Rowina didn't turn on the recorder for the entire afternoon.

530
00:24:00,430 --> 00:24:04,950
She sat with Jago in his office on the 13th floor of a glass building in downtown Savannah

531
00:24:04,950 --> 00:24:08,290
and they talked about things no interview called for.

532
00:24:08,290 --> 00:24:12,810
A cousin he had never saw, a book she had read 12 times in her teens,

533
00:24:13,370 --> 00:24:15,810
the specific smell of the coffee her mother used to make.

534
00:24:16,170 --> 00:24:19,930
Jago poured her coffee that afternoon in a way she hadn't taught him,

535
00:24:20,110 --> 00:24:23,430
half a spoon of sugar, a splash of milk, very hot.

536
00:24:23,910 --> 00:24:27,890
Rowina looked at the cup, looked at him, and didn't ask how he knew.

537
00:24:28,310 --> 00:24:31,730
Nieve let the answer slip a week later, in the mansions kitchen,

538
00:24:32,290 --> 00:24:36,890
while drying a crystal glass with the attention of someone handling something bigger than a glass.

539
00:24:36,890 --> 00:24:39,470
He's been sleeping better since you've been coming.

540
00:24:39,970 --> 00:24:42,530
The housekeeper didn't look at Rowina as she said it.

541
00:24:42,750 --> 00:24:45,070
It's not a compliment, it's an observation.

542
00:24:45,990 --> 00:24:48,650
Rowina laughed softly without breath to answer.

543
00:24:49,090 --> 00:24:50,790
Do you want to know something miss?

544
00:24:51,110 --> 00:24:53,310
Nieve continued, putting the glass away.

545
00:24:53,750 --> 00:24:56,710
It's been a long time since anyone asked him how his day was.

546
00:24:57,030 --> 00:25:00,230
He would be grateful, even if he didn't know how to thank you.

547
00:25:00,590 --> 00:25:03,270
Rowina's hand trembled slightly on the handle of her mug.

548
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:06,070
She set the mug down on the marble with doubled care.

549
00:25:06,070 --> 00:25:08,450
The charity event took place on a Thursday.

550
00:25:08,930 --> 00:25:12,850
It was an auction in aid of a children's hospital in a vaulted ceiling tall,

551
00:25:13,130 --> 00:25:16,450
where the candleabras seemed too heavy for the wire that held them.

552
00:25:16,730 --> 00:25:19,590
Rowina wore a dark green dress borrowed from Marlo's sister,

553
00:25:20,050 --> 00:25:24,870
and Jago appeared at her side at the entrance, as if he'd matched the exact time to his own watch.

554
00:25:25,410 --> 00:25:27,750
Odez Masha'a arrived 20 minutes later.

555
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:30,490
Rowina saw her approach from the other side of the hall,

556
00:25:30,730 --> 00:25:35,250
greeting people with thin kisses, a champagne coloured dress moving like liquid.

557
00:25:35,250 --> 00:25:40,730
Odez stopped in front of Rowina, looked her up and down with a smile too polite to be polite,

558
00:25:41,210 --> 00:25:44,070
and said in a tone that carried through the three nearest people,

559
00:25:44,550 --> 00:25:49,030
you hold up well dear. A borrowed dress in a hall of this caliber isn't for just anyone.

560
00:25:49,450 --> 00:25:53,210
I hope the night is kind to you. The air in the hall became specific.

561
00:25:53,710 --> 00:25:55,710
Two women near the buffet stopped chewing.

562
00:25:56,450 --> 00:26:00,350
Rowina felt the blood rise up her neck and choose between turning into fury

563
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:01,990
and turning into dignity.

564
00:26:01,990 --> 00:26:06,350
Before she could decide, Jago's hand touched the small of her back,

565
00:26:06,770 --> 00:26:10,130
firm, without theatrical possession, just presence,

566
00:26:10,710 --> 00:26:13,870
and he took half a step forward, shoulder pressed against hers.

567
00:26:14,310 --> 00:26:18,130
Odez, he said, and his voice was no longer lower than usual,

568
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:23,130
only stripped of anything amiable. If you have any doubts about the woman I came with,

569
00:26:23,370 --> 00:26:28,330
put those doubts to me directly. Rowina owes you no explanation about where she buys any dress,

570
00:26:28,330 --> 00:26:34,550
neither do you. Odez parted her lips, and something inside her smile gave way for half a second,

571
00:26:35,050 --> 00:26:40,810
before recomposing. Now touch Jago, it was a compliment. It wasn't. He didn't raise his tone,

572
00:26:41,090 --> 00:26:46,770
he didn't need to. Two people nearby rediscovered a sudden fascination with their own shoes. Odez

573
00:26:46,770 --> 00:26:52,130
nodded, murmured a phrase about finding a friend and withdrew. Jago didn't move his hand

574
00:26:52,130 --> 00:26:57,350
from Rowina's back for a few more seconds, and in those seconds she felt everything. His thumb

575
00:26:57,350 --> 00:27:03,210
resting exactly on the seam of her dress, the heat of his palm, the silent weight of being chosen

576
00:27:03,210 --> 00:27:08,850
there before an entire room. When he moved his hand away it was slow. Rowina drew a breath.

577
00:27:09,210 --> 00:27:15,430
You didn't need to. I did actually, he answered, without looking at her. She knew what she was doing.

578
00:27:15,910 --> 00:27:21,590
The rest of the night passed in waves. Rowina won a small lot with the money she had, a pair of glass

579
00:27:21,590 --> 00:27:26,150
earrings no one wanted. Jago won nothing. He just watched her from afar,

580
00:27:26,150 --> 00:27:32,010
from across the hall, and every time she raised her eyes, he was already looking. They returned

581
00:27:32,010 --> 00:27:36,750
to the mansion around midnight. She went up to the guest room and stood for a long time in front

582
00:27:36,750 --> 00:27:42,730
of the open suitcase on the floor, at the bottom of it, under two folded blouses and a pair of

583
00:27:42,730 --> 00:27:50,190
old shoes was the file. Brown, no label, tied with a rubber band, Rowina pulled it into her lap,

584
00:27:50,570 --> 00:27:55,330
sat on the rug and stayed looking. She didn't open it. She ran her thumb along the edge,

585
00:27:55,330 --> 00:28:00,350
drew a deep breath, and returned the file to the bottom of the suitcase. She folded the

586
00:28:00,350 --> 00:28:05,370
blouses over it with exaggerated care, as if covering it were enough to undo what laberneth.

587
00:28:05,870 --> 00:28:11,930
Her phone on the nightstand vibrated. Rowina glanced sideways. A missed call. Then another.

588
00:28:12,350 --> 00:28:17,410
Then a third one she watched arrive. Pollis Vaughan's name blinking on the screen like a silent alarm.

589
00:28:17,770 --> 00:28:22,150
She let it ring until it stopped. She kept looking at the phone until the light went out.

590
00:28:22,150 --> 00:28:29,110
When she lowered her head again, the phone vibrated a fourth time. A fifth. Rowina closed her eyes.

591
00:28:29,610 --> 00:28:35,930
Across the corridor, someone walked slowly. Bear feet on the wood. She knew who steps they were,

592
00:28:36,130 --> 00:28:41,970
and she didn't open the door. The phone kept. Chapter 4 The File She Wouldn't Open.

593
00:28:43,330 --> 00:28:49,030
ringing. Pollis Vaughan's fifth call came just after dawn, and this time, Rowina answered.

594
00:28:49,030 --> 00:28:53,370
She was sitting on the floor of the guest room, still in the wrinkled green dress.

595
00:28:53,770 --> 00:28:58,210
The glass earrings in her lap, the phone trembling in her hand for the sixth time.

596
00:28:58,690 --> 00:29:03,230
The rug beneath her smelled of old lavender, the kind of lavender that isn't perfume.

597
00:29:03,870 --> 00:29:10,270
It's time. You vanished, said Hollis without a greeting. His voice had that measured calm that preceded

598
00:29:10,270 --> 00:29:15,730
firings. I haven't heard your voice in three weeks. Don't give me behind schedule. It's behind

599
00:29:15,730 --> 00:29:21,930
schedule. That's not the point. The point is the material. Where is it? I'm working. You're not.

600
00:29:22,430 --> 00:29:27,630
Rowina closed her eyes and rested her forehead on her knee. The knee was cold through the wrinkled fabric.

601
00:29:28,130 --> 00:29:33,210
Outside the garden hadn't quite woken up yet. A shallow grey light spread across the window,

602
00:29:33,630 --> 00:29:39,350
as if the day was still convincing itself to arrive. Pollis. Rowina. He drew a deep breath on

603
00:29:39,350 --> 00:29:44,730
the other end of the line. I backed you. I bought the ticket. Pade for the hotel the first weekend,

604
00:29:44,730 --> 00:29:49,990
kept your shift going with Marlo covering three straight shifts. I'm not a benefactor. I'm an editor.

605
00:29:50,570 --> 00:29:54,970
And an editor needs to deliver. Either you send me something by Monday night or I'll have to

606
00:29:54,970 --> 00:30:01,010
make a decision neither of us once. She didn't answer right away. Outside, a bird insisted on the

607
00:30:01,010 --> 00:30:06,310
same short note near the window. And Rowina caught herself thinking about how Jago used to be late

608
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:11,050
with the coffee whenever there was a bird nearby. He'd stand out on the porch for a moment,

609
00:30:11,050 --> 00:30:16,850
listening. The cup forgotten in his hand. She shouldn't have noticed that. She had noticed.

610
00:30:17,450 --> 00:30:23,570
I heard you. She said finally. You didn't. Hollis answered. But you will. Monday night,

611
00:30:23,930 --> 00:30:29,390
headline or resignation. The hung up first. Rowina kept looking at the phone for a length of time

612
00:30:29,390 --> 00:30:34,870
she couldn't measure. The reflection of her own distorted face on the black screen. She stood up

613
00:30:34,870 --> 00:30:39,950
slowly. She walked to the suitcase which was half open on a wooden chair near the dresser. She pulled

614
00:30:39,950 --> 00:30:45,890
a brown file out by the rubber band sat down again on the rug and rested the file on her own thighs.

615
00:30:46,430 --> 00:30:51,890
Her hands were still this time. Stiller than she expected. She untied the rubber band slowly.

616
00:30:52,470 --> 00:30:58,630
She opened the first flap. Papers. Clippings of balance sheets. Photocopies Hollis had obtained

617
00:30:58,630 --> 00:31:04,470
from some discreet source. Notes in small handwriting written by herself before she met Jago Quint.

618
00:31:04,990 --> 00:31:09,610
In a gray, noisy newsroom where the coffee was bad, and ambition still seemed enough to

619
00:31:09,610 --> 00:31:15,150
the bills. Rowina read two lines of her own field notebook and didn't recognize the woman who had

620
00:31:15,150 --> 00:31:20,870
written that. She closed the file. She tied the rubber band again. She put everything back at the bottom

621
00:31:20,870 --> 00:31:24,810
of the suitcase. The partner's dinner was scheduled for that same night.

622
00:31:25,270 --> 00:31:30,350
Nieve came up in the late afternoon with a dress hanging from a velvet hanger. Deep wine,

623
00:31:30,850 --> 00:31:35,810
straight neckline, sleeves to the elbow. The fabric had a specific weight to the touch.

624
00:31:35,810 --> 00:31:40,570
That weight of something chosen with attention. Rowina looked at her without understanding.

625
00:31:41,190 --> 00:31:45,250
From the master said Nieve and set the hanger on the chair against the wall,

626
00:31:45,690 --> 00:31:49,570
he asked me to leave it here. He said the miss isn't obliged to wear it.

627
00:31:50,050 --> 00:31:55,370
Rowina laughed without joy. And if I don't wear it, he won't ask why, said Nieve,

628
00:31:55,810 --> 00:32:00,350
with a half smile that didn't quite complete itself. But he'll notice. He notices.

629
00:32:00,950 --> 00:32:04,970
She wore the dress. She couldn't decide whether it was surrender or courage,

630
00:32:04,970 --> 00:32:09,330
and she chose not to decide. The mansion's dining room had 18 places,

631
00:32:09,890 --> 00:32:14,270
and a table that was a vanished skating rink. There were six partners, three wives,

632
00:32:14,850 --> 00:32:19,390
Silas Ashford at one end in the same gray suit as always, and the face of someone who has already

633
00:32:19,390 --> 00:32:24,790
seen far too much, without being surprised by anything. And you door a quint at the other end,

634
00:32:25,210 --> 00:32:30,490
seated as though the seat had been built around her. Rowina entered beside Jego. She was introduced

635
00:32:30,490 --> 00:32:36,350
by him in a sentence that left no gap. Rowina Pike, she's with me. It wasn't a description.

636
00:32:36,930 --> 00:32:41,810
It was a signature. The dinner advanced through courses she barely tasted. There was talk

637
00:32:41,810 --> 00:32:47,330
of an acquisition up north of a land auction near the river of a niece's wedding in Charleston.

638
00:32:47,930 --> 00:32:53,270
Rowina answered when addressed and listened when not addressed. The wine was too good to be wasted

639
00:32:53,270 --> 00:32:59,050
on anxiety, so she drank slowly and kept her spine straight. At some point between the second

640
00:32:59,050 --> 00:33:04,370
course and the third, Jego's hand found hers on top of the white table cloth. He didn't hold

641
00:33:04,370 --> 00:33:10,190
it halfway or hide it under the table. He left his hand resting on top of her hand in full view of

642
00:33:10,190 --> 00:33:15,290
everyone, and went on talking to the partner to his left, as if the hand was some object he'd

643
00:33:15,290 --> 00:33:21,330
found along the way, and decided to keep. Silas noticed first. Rowina saw the small flicker in

644
00:33:21,330 --> 00:33:29,030
the lawyer's eyes, almost invisible, followed by a throat clearing that made way for nothing. You

645
00:33:29,030 --> 00:33:33,550
re-arcted and take her eyes off her plate, but her fork paused half a second in the air,

646
00:33:33,950 --> 00:33:39,530
and resumed moving with a care Rowina had learned to interpret as reading. You'dora read people.

647
00:33:39,970 --> 00:33:44,910
She did it all the time, without appearing to be doing it. After coffee the partner's rose

648
00:33:44,910 --> 00:33:51,150
for cigars, and the wives went off to another parlor. Rowina went up alone. In the corridor she

649
00:33:51,150 --> 00:33:55,530
crossed paths with Silas, who carried a folder under his arm and a look she couldn't decipher.

650
00:33:55,530 --> 00:34:00,690
The kind of look that holds more than one interpretation, and gives away none.

651
00:34:01,270 --> 00:34:07,030
Good night, Miss. He said. Good night, Mr. Ashford. He seemed to want to say something more.

652
00:34:07,270 --> 00:34:12,150
He weighed the moment, decided against it, and went on down the corridor with the firm stride of

653
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:17,730
someone with a set destination. In the guest room, Rowina shut the door and leaned against it for a

654
00:34:17,730 --> 00:34:22,350
moment. The wood was cold against her back through the fabric of the dress. She thought about

655
00:34:22,350 --> 00:34:27,270
tearing up the notes. She thought about calling Hollis and telling him the story didn't exist.

656
00:34:27,610 --> 00:34:31,790
She thought about telling Jago everything that night, with the wine still in her body and the

657
00:34:31,790 --> 00:34:36,790
courage of exhaustion. She thought about doing none of the three things, and leaving it all for the

658
00:34:36,790 --> 00:34:42,490
train back. She went to the bathroom, took off her makeup with cold water and cotton. Put on a

659
00:34:42,490 --> 00:34:47,450
simple linen-night gown lay down on top of the bed's bread, and stared at the white-washed ceiling

660
00:34:47,450 --> 00:34:54,250
as the house grew quiet. Room, by room. She fell asleep without realizing it. She was

661
00:34:54,250 --> 00:34:59,330
welcome by the sound of the door. There was no knock. The door opened slowly, letting in a thin

662
00:34:59,330 --> 00:35:04,710
band of light from the corridor, and Rowina saw against that light, the silhouette of Jago Quint.

663
00:35:05,250 --> 00:35:09,150
He didn't turn on the room's lamp. He walked to the middle of the room and stopped,

664
00:35:09,650 --> 00:35:16,590
and only then did she notice what was in his hands. The file. Brown, no label, no rubber band now.

665
00:35:16,590 --> 00:35:22,350
Rowina sat up in the bed in a single motion. The air left her chest in an exhalation that

666
00:35:22,350 --> 00:35:28,870
made no sound. How...silence he said without raising his voice, he saw a debt prowling this corridor earlier.

667
00:35:29,330 --> 00:35:35,190
He thought it best I checked before she did. His voice was low. It was calm. It was empty of

668
00:35:35,190 --> 00:35:39,390
anything she could use to hold on to. Jago looked at the file he was carrying,

669
00:35:39,910 --> 00:35:44,790
leaped through a page she recognized without needing to look closely, and put the page back in its

670
00:35:44,790 --> 00:35:49,610
place, with a care that seemed in that moment, the cruelest thing in the world.

671
00:35:50,090 --> 00:35:55,930
Balanced sheets, he said. Copies of old contracts, a list of names with notes beside them.

672
00:35:56,150 --> 00:36:00,990
I recognized at least three of the names. He lifted his eyes to her. This isn't an interview.

673
00:36:01,490 --> 00:36:07,130
It isn't, Rowina answered, because denying it would have been a worse insult. He nodded slightly.

674
00:36:07,750 --> 00:36:13,950
That was all. A single precise nod that didn't judge, and therefore weighed more than any judgment.

675
00:36:13,950 --> 00:36:20,230
You came here for this. I came here for this, she said, and I didn't know I would stop coming here for

676
00:36:20,230 --> 00:36:25,230
it. But I did stop. Weeks ago. I haven't opened that file once since.

677
00:36:25,510 --> 00:36:30,130
Herit doesn't matter, he cut in, and even cutting in he kept his usual low tone.

678
00:36:30,610 --> 00:36:34,370
You opened it yesterday, I heard you open it. I thought you were closing a suitcase.

679
00:36:35,170 --> 00:36:39,210
The silence settled between them, with a specificity, Rowina couldn't fill,

680
00:36:39,210 --> 00:36:44,410
and he didn't try to. Jago. Thank you for coming to Savannah, he said, and that was the

681
00:36:44,410 --> 00:36:49,810
sentence that went through her from side to side. Thank you for the weeks. The interview is paid for.

682
00:36:50,130 --> 00:36:54,530
If you still want it, I only ask that you leave tomorrow morning before my mother comes down

683
00:36:54,530 --> 00:36:59,770
for coffee. She opened her mouth, closed it, opened it again. Don't do this like this.

684
00:37:00,410 --> 00:37:05,810
Like what? Without yelling at me. He considered the sentence. He took too long to answer

685
00:37:05,810 --> 00:37:10,930
the kind of delay that is an answer in itself. If I yell you'll be able to think I'm still angry.

686
00:37:11,470 --> 00:37:16,590
His voice found a note she had never heard in him, too low to have a name. I don't want you to

687
00:37:16,590 --> 00:37:21,650
think that. I want you to leave knowing exactly what stayed behind. It was worse than yelling.

688
00:37:22,170 --> 00:37:26,390
It was worse than anything she could have predicted that week or in any week before it.

689
00:37:26,730 --> 00:37:31,470
Jago set the file on the dresser near the door, with a precision that seemed calculated to make

690
00:37:31,470 --> 00:37:36,970
no noise. He didn't return it to her hand. He didn't take it with him. He left it there.

691
00:37:37,170 --> 00:37:41,770
In the middle of the way, like an exposed piece of evidence, neither of them needed to examine

692
00:37:41,770 --> 00:37:47,330
anymore. Then he turned toward the door. Leave tomorrow. The door closed behind him with the most

693
00:37:47,330 --> 00:37:52,390
polite noise a door has ever produced in the entire world. Rowena remained sitting on the bed.

694
00:37:52,810 --> 00:37:57,910
Her hands opened on the bed spread. A heart beating in a rhythm she didn't recognize as her own.

695
00:37:57,910 --> 00:38:03,970
Outside in the corridor, his footsteps moved away slowly. No hurry, no hesitation,

696
00:38:04,650 --> 00:38:09,630
and at some point between her room and his room, they stopped for a second before continuing.

697
00:38:10,230 --> 00:38:14,710
She didn't cry. Not yet. She kept looking at the file on top of the dresser,

698
00:38:14,930 --> 00:38:18,610
like someone staring at an animal that had followed her from too far away,

699
00:38:19,010 --> 00:38:24,070
to now pretend it was a stranger. Outside the window, the garden of the quint mansion,

700
00:38:24,670 --> 00:38:30,050
breathed the humid night. The smell of earth and jasmine rising with the breeze off the river.

701
00:38:30,470 --> 00:38:36,010
Somewhere near the water, a real owl called out once. Rowena thought of the glass owl set with red

702
00:38:36,010 --> 00:38:41,310
stone, tucked in a dark velvet box at the bottom of her bag, and felt that this was the memory

